<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Albert Park/Radisson Heights</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Established back in 1910, the community in Albert Park/Radisson Heights possesses a distinctive old-world charm that sets it a class apart from the rest of the neighborhoods in Calgary. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The neighborhood is surrounded by 17 Avenue SE to the south, Memorial Drive to the north, Deerfoot Trail to the west, and the community of <a href="/forest-lawn.php">Forest Lawn</a>&nbsp;to the east.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Residents in Albert Park/Radisson Heights have a plethora of housing options ranging from single-family detached homes to apartments and condominiums that are regularly available at an average price of $350,000. </p>
        </div>
